Q3: The Text Analyzer
Description:
Write a program that accepts a sentence string and performs three distinct analyzes using
helper functions:
1. Word Count: Count total words (based on whitespace).
2. Vowel Count: Count total vowels (a, e, i, o, u).
3. Reverse: Print the reversed string.
Input Format:
‚óè A single string (may contain spaces).
Sample Test Case 1:
Input:
Hello World
Output:
Words: 2
Vowels: 3
Reversed: dlroW olleH
Sample Test Case 2:
Input:
C Programming
Output:
Words: 2
Vowels: 3
Reversed: gnimmargorP C





#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <ctype.h>
int main(){
    char sentence[1000];
    printf("Please type the sentence: ");
    scanf(" %[^\n]", sentence);
    int wordCount = 0;
    for(int i = 0; sentence[i] != '\0'; i++){
        if(sentence[i] == ' '){ 
            wordCount++;
        }
    }
    printf("Total number of words in the sentence is: %d \n \n", wordCount + 1);
    int vowelCount = 0;
    for(int i = 0; sentence[i] != '\0'; i++){
        if(sentence[i] == 'a' || sentence[i] == 'e' || sentence[i] == 'i' ||sentence[i] == 'o' || sentence[i] == 'u' || sentence[i] == 'A' || sentence[i] == 'E' || sentence[i] == 'I' || sentence[i] == 'O' || sentence[i] == 'U'){
            vowelCount++;
        }
    }
    printf("Total number of vowels in the sentence is: %d\n\n", vowelCount);
    int len = strlen(sentence);
    for(int i = len -1; i >= 0 ; i--){
        printf("%c", sentence[i]);
    }
    return 0;
}
